class Solution {
    public boolean isSubstringPresent(String s) {
        String reversed = new StringBuilder(s).reverse().toString();
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length() - 1; i++) {
            if (reversed.indexOf(s.substring(i, i + 2)) != -1) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates over the input string once, creating a reversed copy of it. It checks every substring of length 2 in the original string to see if it exists in the reversed string, returning true as soon as it finds a match. The use of `indexOf` allows for an efficient search in the reversed string.
